<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="424" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="424">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,150,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="424">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species was described on the basis of 
<specimenCount box="[797,914,150,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="424" type="male">eight male</specimenCount>
specimens from south 
<collectingCountry box="[1172,1260,150,176]" name="Nigeria" pageId="8" pageNumber="424">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
. The specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[214,289,186,212]" name="Gabon" pageId="8" pageNumber="424">Gabon</collectingCountry>
considerably enlarge its range of distribution. No female was collected (the supposed discovery of a female suggested by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kruger, M." box="[387,548,222,249]" pageId="8" pageNumber="424" pagination="1 - 176" refId="ref7647" refString="Kruger, M. (2015) Generic classification of Afrotropical footman moths sensu stricto (Lepidoptera: Erebidae: Arctiinae: Lithosiini (partim )). Transvaal Museum Monograph, 15, 1 - 176." type="journal article" year="2015">Krüger (2015)</bibRefCitation>
is dealt with in the discussion).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,150,285]" box="[199,784,258,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="424">
Genitalia are figured in 
<bibRefCitation author="Durante, M. A. &amp; Panzera, S." box="[467,780,258,285]" pageId="8" pageNumber="424" pagination="465 - 472" refId="ref6987" refString="Durante, M. A. &amp; Panzera, S. (2001 b) I Lepidotteri del Delta del Niger (terzo contributo) (Lepidoptera, Arctiidae, Lithosiinae). Lambillionea, 101 (3), 465 - 472." type="journal article" year="2001">Durante &amp; Panzera (2001b)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
